# 📧 Bulk Email Sender with Attachment and Personalization

This is a Django-based email-sending tool that allows you to send personalized emails in bulk using an Excel file. Each email can include dynamic name insertion (`{{name}}`), attachments (PDF/images), and duplicate prevention using a unique hash. It supports a kill switch to stop sending at any time.

---

## 🚀 Features

- ✅ Send bulk emails using an Excel (.xlsx) file
- ✅ Personalize emails using `{{name}}` placeholder
- ✅ Optional file attachment (PDF, Image, etc.)
- ✅ Skip duplicate messages (via hashing)
- ✅ Stop sending in real-time with a kill switch
- ✅ Reconnect on SMTP failure
- ✅ Gmail SMTP supported


## 📥 How to Use

1: Run these commands in the terminal

    python -m venv env
    env\Scripts\activate 
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    python manage.py runserver    



 2: Open the form
    Visit:

        http://127.0.0.1:8000/

    You will see a form like:

        Sender Email (e.g. yourgmail@gmail.com)

        Password (App password recommended for Gmail)

        Subject

        Message ({{name}} will be replaced by the name from Excel)

        Excel file (must have column named Email and optionally Name)

        Attachment (optional)



## ⚠️ Important Notes


    Gmail limits sending to 500 emails/day for free accounts.

    Repeated failures may trigger Gmail security lockouts.
